t their PIN or password, or when their BIOS or boot records change.","pos":[1639,1785]},{"content":"The following groups might be interested in using MBAM to manage BitLocker:","pos":[1787,1862]},{"content":"Administrators, IT security professionals, and compliance officers who are responsible for ensuring that confidential data is not disclosed without authorization","pos":[1868,2029]},{"content":"Administrators who are responsible for computer security in remote or branch offices","pos":[2035,2119]},{"content":"Administrators who are responsible for client computers that are running Windows","pos":[2125,2205]},{"content":"Note","pos":[2209,2213]},{"content":"BitLocker is not explained in detail in this MBAM documentation.","pos":[2218,2282]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>BitLocker Drive Encryption Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=225013)</ept>.","pos":[2283,2396]},{"pos":[2451,2477],"content":"What’s new in MBAM 2.5 SP1"},{"content":"This section describes the new features in MBAM 2.5 SP1.","pos":[2480,2536]},{"content":"Newly Supported Languages for the MBAM 2.5 SP1 Client","pos":[2542,2595]},{"content":"The following additional languages are now supported in MBAM 2.5 SP1 for the MBAM Client only, including the Self-Service Portal:","pos":[2597,2726]},{"content":"Czech (Czech Republic) cs-CZ","pos":[2728,2756]},{"content":"Danish (Denmark) da-DK","pos":[2758,2780]},{"content":"Dutch (Netherlands) nl-NL","pos":[2782,2807]},{"content":"Finnish (Finland) fi-FI","pos":[2809,2832]},{"content":"Greek (Greece) el-GR","pos":[2834,2854]},{"content":"Hungarian (Hungary) hu-HU","pos":[2856,2881]},{"content":"Norwegian, Bokmål (Norway) nb-NO","pos":[2883,2915]},{"content":"Polish (Poland) pl-PL","pos":[2917,2938]},{"content":"Portuguese (Portugal) pt-PT","pos":[2940,2967]},{"content":"Slovak (Slovakia) sk-SK","pos":[2969,2992]},{"content":"Slovenian (Slovenia) sl-SI","pos":[2994,3020]},{"content":"Swedish (Sweden