dition, Group Policy must be set to prevent the OwnerAuth from being deleted locally.","pos":[4474,4564]},{"content":"In Windows 7, MBAM must own the TPM to automatically escrow TPM OwnerAuth information in the MBAM database.","pos":[4566,4673]},{"content":"If MBAM does not own the TPM and Active Directory (AD) backup of the TPM is configured through Group Policy, you must use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>MBAM Active Directory (AD) Data Import cmdlets<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to copy TPM OwnerAuth from AD into the MBAM database.","pos":[4674,4904]},{"content":"These are five new PowerShell cmdlets that pre-populate MBAM databases with the Volume recovery and TPM owner information stored in Active Directory.","pos":[4905,5054]},{"pos":[5056,5162],"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>MBAM 2.5 Security Considerations<ept id=\"p1\">](mbam-25-security-considerations.md#bkmk-tpm)</ept>."},{"content":"MBAM can automatically unlock the TPM after a lockout","pos":[5168,5221]},{"content":"On computers running TPM 1.2, you can now configure MBAM to automatically unlock the TPM in case of a lockout.","pos":[5223,5333]},{"content":"If the TPM lockout auto reset feature is enabled, MBAM can detect that a user is locked out and then get the OwnerAuth password from the MBAM database to automatically unlock the TPM for the user.","pos":[5334,5530]},{"content":"This feature must be enabled on both the server side and in Group Policy on the client side.","pos":[5532,5624]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>MBAM 2.5 Security Considerations<ept id=\"p1\">](mbam-25-security-considerations.md#bkmk-autounlock)</ept>.","pos":[5625,5738]},{"content":"Support for FIPS-compliant BitLocker numerical password protectors","pos":[5744,5810]},{"content":"In MBAM 2.5, support was added for Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS)-compliant BitLocker recovery keys on devices running the Windows 8.1 operating system.","pos":[5812,5980]},{"content":"However, Windows did not implement FIPS-compliant recovery keys in Windows 7.","pos":[5981,6058]},{"content":"Therefore, Windows 7 and Windows 8 devices still required a Data Recovery Agent (DRA) protector for recovery.","pos":[6059,6168]},{"content":"The Windows team has backported FIPS-compliant recovery keys with a hotfix, and MBAM 2.5 SP1 has added support for them as well.","pos":[6170,6298]},{"content":"Note","pos":[6302,6306]},{"content":"Client computers that are running the Windows 8 operating system still require a DRA protector since the hotfix was not backported to that OS.","pos":[6311,6453]},{"content":"See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Hotfix Package 2 for BitLocker Administration and Monitoring 2.5<ept id=\"p1\">](https://support.microsoft.com/kb/3015477)</ept> to download and install the BitLocker hotfix for Windows 7 and Windows 8 computers.","pos":[6454,6650]},{"content":"For information about DRA, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Using Data Recovery Agents with BitLocker<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=393557)</ept>.","pos":[6651,6773]},{"content":"To enable FIPS compliance in your organization, you must configure the Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) Group Policy settings.","pos":[6778,6918]},{"content":"For configuration instructions, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>BitLocker Group Policy Settings<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=393560)</ept>.","pos":[6919,7036]},{"content":"Customize pre-boot recovery message and URL with new Group Policy setting","pos":[7042,7115]},{"content":"A new Group Policy setting, <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Configure pre-boot recovery message and URL<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, lets you configure a custom recovery message or specify a URL that is then displayed on the pre-boot BitLocker recovery screen when the OS drive is locked.","pos":[7117,7349]},{"content":"This setting is only available on client computers running Windows 10.","pos":[7350,7420]},{"content":"If you enable this policy setting, you can you can select one of these options for the pre-boot recovery message:","pos":[7422,7535]},{"pos":[7541,7663],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Use custom recovery message<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Select this option to include a custom message in the pre-boot BitLocker recovery screen."},{"pos":[7669,7804],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Use custom recovery URL<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Select this option to replace the default URL that is displayed in the pre-boot BitLocker recovery screen."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Use default recovery message and URL<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Select this option to display the default BitLocker recovery message and URL in the pre-boot BitLocker recovery screen.","pos":[7810,7971]},{"content":"If you previously configured a custom recovery message or URL and want to revert to the default message, you must enable this policy and select this option.","pos":[7972,8128]},{"content":"The new Group Policy setting is located in the following GPO node: <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Computer Configuration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph1\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Policies<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph2\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Administrative Templates<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph3\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>Windows Components<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph4\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p5\">**</bpt>MDOP MBAM (BitLocker Management)<ept id=\"p5\">**</ept> <ph id=\"ph5\">&amp;gt;</ph> <bpt id=\"p6\">**</bpt>Operating System Drive<ept id=\"p6\">**</ept>.","pos":[8130,8378]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Planning for MBAM 2.5 Group Policy Requirements<ept id=\"p1\">](planning-for-mbam-25-group-policy-requirements.md)</ept>.","pos":[8379,8506]},{"content":"MBAM added support for Used Space Encryption","pos":[8512,8556]},{"content":"In MBAM 2.5 SP1, if you enable Used Space Encryption via BitLocker Group Policy, the MBAM Client honors it.","pos":[855